  "body": "\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth 1.8.12`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nGeth synced successfully\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nGeth always left behind around 100k blocks\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nnohup geth --cache 4096\r\n\r\nI had ran the syncing for a week or so, I thought It needed some times to fully synced to the net, but I think there is some issue on my setup\r\n\r\nNB : I ran with `--cache 1536` before (as I only have 4GB ram), it crashed and finally I added 12GB swap and ran with `--cache 4096`, but doesnt seem to be working too\r\n\r\nAnyone here encounter same issue ?\r\n\r\n",
